Simple way to test what is written in the topic sensor-reading the Akka endpoint. 
Requires running Kafka and <https://github.com/mspringma/hackzurich-sensordataanalysis/tree/master/sensor-ingestion>.

Spark Interpreter must be configured with depency

> org.apache.kafka:kafka_2.10:jar:0.10.0.0

See also <https://docs.mesosphere.com/1.7/usage/service-guides/kafka/connecting-clients/>

paragraphs.text:
import org.apache.zookeeper.ZooKeeper
import scala.collection.JavaConversions._
import kafka.utils.Json

def extractConnection(zkData: String): String = {
    val brokerInfo = Json.parseFull(zkData).get.asInstanceOf[Map[String, Any]]
    val host = brokerInfo("host").asInstanceOf[String]
    val port = brokerInfo("port").asInstanceOf[Int]
    s"$host:$port"
}

val zk = new ZooKeeper("master.mesos:2181/dcos-service-kafka", 10000, null)
val ids = zk.getChildren("/brokers/ids", false)
val connections = scala.collection.mutable.ListBuffer.empty[String]

for (id <- ids) {
    connections += (extractConnection(new String(zk.getData("/brokers/ids/" + id, false, null))))
}
val bootstrapServers = connections.mkString(",")

paragraphs.title: Create Consumer
paragraphs.text:
import java.util.Properties
import org.apache.kafka.clients.consumer._

val  consumerProps = new Properties()
consumerProps.put("bootstrap.servers", bootstrapServers)
  
consumerProps.put("key.deserializer", "org.apache.kafka.common.serialization.StringDeserializer")
consumerProps.put("value.deserializer", "org.apache.kafka.common.serialization.StringDeserializer")

// setting a new group id is easiest way to say "I'm just interested in new stuff"
consumerProps.put("group.id", "test-client-consumer-2")

val consumer = new KafkaConsumer[String, String](consumerProps)

Interact with same topic on shell on DC/OS master node
paragraphs.text:
%md
To observe somewhere else, you can actually observe on the shell the topic

> ssh-into-dcos-master.sh

> docker run -it mesosphere/kafka-client

> ./kafka-console-consumer.sh --zookeeper master.mesos:2181/dcos-service-kafka --topic sensor-reading

And you can end with Ctrl-C and post also a new message to the topic through the endpoint

> curl --data '{"sensor":"dummy", "data":"nothing"}' --request POST --basic --user hackzurich http://ec2-54-183-149-224.us-west-1.compute.amazonaws.com:8083/sensorReading/curl
